&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site Nurse Practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity to recruit a Site Nurse Practitioner (SNP) to join the Inpatient Services team at Guy’s and St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a duty SNP you will spend your time;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being part of the clinical response team providing clinical support to acutely unwell patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and coordinating the hospital sites on a day to day basis, including serious and major incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating patient flow through the emergency and elective pathways across the Trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing senior support and leadership to patients, visitors and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides a 24:7 site response and coordination role via the site control room. You will therefore need to demonstrate the ability to manage and lead on untoward and emergency site incidents. This will include managing risk, decision making and activating business continuity plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also provide leadership and support to all staff groups and out of hours will be the senior nurse on duty for the hospital and you will also act as silver command out of hours for our community sites and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will fully support you in gaining and developing these skill sets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To discuss the role further please contact the Senior Site Practitioner team via the Inpatient Services Office Manager on 020 7188 3204.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November (midnight)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSenior Site Nurse Practitioners via the Inpatient Services Office ManagerTelephone number02071883204Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Site Practitioner team via the Inpatient Services Office Manager on 020 7188 3204.&lt;/p&gt;
